<TITLE> WFP intensifies food distribution </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 21 (bdnews24.com) - The World Food Programme and Bangladesh Air Force will airdrop more 75 tons of high energy biscuits to cyclone-hit people, the WFP said in a statement Wednesday. The WFP initiated a second round of food distribution. "We have already started a second round of distribution of 105 additional tons of biscuits to feed 465,000 people in the four most-affected districts," said Douglas Brodrick, WFP representative in Bangladesh. Caritas will provide Tk 10 crore in emergency relief to assist 23,500 families worst affected by Cyclone Sidr, the NGO said in a statement. The nongovernmental organisation will target the worst cyclone-hit areas of the country, including Patuakhali, Barguna and Bagerhat. The aid organisation will also assist in job creation schemes through projects to repair damaged roads, schools and shelters. bdnew
